00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,952
Characters, actions, occupations and events in this series are fictional and created for entertainment purposes only.

2
00:00:09,952 --> 00:00:14,841
They are not intended to urge or promote any behavior in the series.

3
00:00:14,841 --> 00:00:17,557
Viewer discretion is advised.

4
00:00:18,621 --> 00:00:21,013
If this movie was aired in our universe,

5
00:00:21,013 --> 00:00:22,691
it would make millions by now.

6
00:00:22,691 --> 00:00:25,101
If it wasn’t for you, this movie wouldn’t have happened.

7
00:00:25,101 --> 00:00:27,130
It’s life to meet and part.

8
00:00:27,130 --> 00:00:29,024
I’m so proud to work with you guys.

9
00:00:29,024 --> 00:00:30,916
What are you gonna do now?

10
00:00:31,070 --> 00:00:32,680
I’m moving back home.

11
00:00:32,840 --> 00:00:36,968
If I stop writing screenplays, I won’t be able to cover the rent.

12
00:00:39,276 --> 00:00:40,000
Talay,

13
00:00:41,276 --> 00:00:43,056
would you like to move in with me?

14
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:02,612
Your clothes are colorful.

15
00:01:04,521 --> 00:01:06,745
They’re making my room a lot livelier.

16
00:01:10,002 --> 00:01:10,810
Wait.

17
00:01:12,658 --> 00:01:14,410
Not my room anymore.

18
00:01:16,220 --> 00:01:17,352
Our room.

19
00:01:18,497 --> 00:01:20,080
What are you saying?

20
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:21,341
I’m getting goosebumps.

21
00:01:22,993 --> 00:01:24,560
You said you would watch a movie.

22
00:01:25,852 --> 00:01:27,488
I am.

23
00:01:28,163 --> 00:01:31,280
I prepared popped rice for you already.

24
00:01:43,449 --> 00:01:44,680
Tun!

25
00:01:45,149 --> 00:01:46,673
Why don’t you eat it normally?

26
00:01:47,608 --> 00:01:49,020
I don’t want my hands messy.

27
00:01:50,531 --> 00:01:51,635
Can I borrow yours?

28
00:02:03,508 --> 00:02:04,724
My hands are clean.

29
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,344
I won’t be the only one with sticky hands.

30
00:02:10,387 --> 00:02:11,240
What?

31
00:02:33,733 --> 00:02:36,000
We should stop eating popped rice.

32
00:02:38,410 --> 00:02:39,654
Better eat something else.

33
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:02,600
We should stop watching the movie.

34
00:03:09,257 --> 00:03:10,725
Let’s get ready for bed.

35
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,024
Here.

36
00:03:47,734 --> 00:03:52,954
Do you know who puts toothpaste on each other’s toothbrushes?

37
00:03:54,550 --> 00:03:55,458
Who?

38
00:03:56,420 --> 00:03:58,420
Come on. Think.

39
00:03:59,769 --> 00:04:01,041
Anyone.

40
00:04:04,156 --> 00:04:08,620
Who is the last person we see before bed

41
00:04:09,201 --> 00:04:12,112
and the first person we see after waking up?

42
00:04:13,601 --> 00:04:14,623
Can’t be anyone else.

43
00:04:15,601 --> 00:04:18,000
Tun, what are you saying?

44
00:04:20,857 --> 00:04:22,101
Just brush your teeth.

45
00:04:45,448 --> 00:04:46,888
Tun!

46
00:04:47,479 --> 00:04:48,807
Enough.

47
00:04:49,001 --> 00:04:50,640
That latter part doesn’t sound right.

48
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:56,280
Do you want me to live with you or do you want something 18+?

49
00:04:57,942 --> 00:04:59,298
Come on.

50
00:04:59,298 --> 00:05:00,590
Anything can happen.

51
00:05:01,643 --> 00:05:02,887
No.

52
00:05:03,948 --> 00:05:06,508
Us living together will result in fighting all the time.

53
00:05:15,825 --> 00:05:16,636
Tun.

54
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:19,092
About the rental,

55
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:21,241
I can help you pay.

56
00:05:22,852 --> 00:05:23,908
No.

57
00:05:25,084 --> 00:05:29,612
I’d feel bad if you just pay and don’t live there with me.

58
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:38,998
Besides,

59
00:05:40,037 --> 00:05:42,401
the reason I want you to move in with me

60
00:05:43,104 --> 00:05:47,232
is that I’m feeling a bit lost as I won’t get to spend time with you anymore.

61
00:05:49,788 --> 00:05:54,000
Seeing you 24/7 is heartwarming.

62
00:06:01,004 --> 00:06:03,004
You should spend time with someone else too.

63
00:06:04,060 --> 00:06:06,284
You might find your portkey.

64
00:06:08,247 --> 00:06:09,967
Don’t you want to go back?

65
00:07:20,162 --> 00:07:22,666
I still can’t find my portkey.

66
00:07:25,331 --> 00:07:28,087
Damn it! I just want to drink so bad.

67
00:07:29,129 --> 00:07:32,529
There, there. Let me give you a warm hug.

68
00:07:32,529 --> 00:07:36,312
Spend the night with me. I’ll give you free fried chicken.

69
00:07:36,312 --> 00:07:37,419
That’s enough. Come here.

70
00:07:37,419 --> 00:07:38,764
Do not take advantage of him.

71
00:07:38,764 --> 00:07:39,791
Come here.

72
00:07:40,351 --> 00:07:41,220
Here.

73
00:07:42,790 --> 00:07:43,894
Why stopping me?

74
00:07:44,195 --> 00:07:45,016
Sit tight.

75
00:07:45,016 --> 00:07:47,455
I’m pretty lonely these days.

76
00:07:47,571 --> 00:07:50,887
Tun has been gone. He doesn’t come at all.

77
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Where is Tun, Talay?

78
00:07:54,681 --> 00:07:56,149
No idea.

79
00:07:56,485 --> 00:07:59,437
Since we disbanded, I haven’t seen him.

80
00:08:00,001 --> 00:08:01,525
He doesn’t pick up my calls.

81
00:08:04,144 --> 00:08:06,676
I haven’t seen him for a week.

82
00:08:07,163 --> 00:08:08,939
My heart is shattered.

83
00:08:08,939 --> 00:08:10,559
Too much. It’s just a week.

84
00:08:10,746 --> 00:08:12,410
Not just a week.

85
00:08:12,609 --> 00:08:18,800
It’s 168 hours or 10,080 minutes or…

86
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,966
Enough.

87
00:08:20,119 --> 00:08:21,720
Do you miss him that much?

88
00:08:22,855 --> 00:08:24,435
You don’t get it.

89
00:08:24,435 --> 00:08:28,863
When we miss someone, a minute feels like a year.

90
00:08:29,622 --> 00:08:30,922
Right, Talay?

91
00:08:33,107 --> 00:08:34,463
- Me?
- Yes.

92
00:08:35,087 --> 00:08:37,703
You two always stick together.

93
00:08:37,703 --> 00:08:41,690
If one is missing, the other one can’t help but feel a bit empty.

94
00:09:06,001 --> 00:09:07,525
Can you sing for me?

95
00:09:07,706 --> 00:09:09,706
I want to hear music from our universe.

96
00:09:09,838 --> 00:09:11,838
Sing it yourself.

97
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:16,048
I want to hear a song you sing.

98
00:09:18,532 --> 00:09:20,308
I’m playing games.

99
00:09:21,598 --> 00:09:23,038
Please, Talay.

100
00:09:23,279 --> 00:09:24,803
It can be your favorite song.

101
00:09:25,198 --> 00:09:26,470
The one by Paradox.

102
00:09:28,069 --> 00:09:28,900
‘Love.’

103
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:31,201
No ‘Love’ now.

104
00:09:31,397 --> 00:09:32,415
Let me play this game first.

105
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,640
You’re mean.

106
00:10:14,684 --> 00:10:16,840
Yeah! The exams are all over.

107
00:10:18,347 --> 00:10:19,479
Right.

108
00:10:20,188 --> 00:10:22,188
Studying for the exams was exhausting.

109
00:10:23,612 --> 00:10:25,612
My agony is finally over.

110
00:10:27,364 --> 00:10:28,484
Are you sure?

111
00:10:29,245 --> 00:10:31,245
You can’t graduate yet, Tess.

112
00:10:32,486 --> 00:10:33,842
Why can’t I?

113
00:10:34,657 --> 00:10:36,125
I have lots of accumulated scores.

114
00:10:36,854 --> 00:10:38,042
I won’t get an F.

115
00:10:38,493 --> 00:10:40,129
Not this term’s courses.

116
00:10:40,129 --> 00:10:42,175
Did you forget you’re missing one more course?

117
00:10:42,175 --> 00:10:43,062
Right.

118
00:10:43,270 --> 00:10:45,680
You said you didn’t want to study too much.

119
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:47,948
So you didn’t enroll in the last English course.

120
00:10:47,948 --> 00:10:48,961
You have to study alone now.

121
00:10:48,961 --> 00:10:52,201
How lonely!

122
00:10:55,933 --> 00:10:56,763
Right.

123
00:10:57,715 --> 00:10:58,885
How lonely.

124
00:11:02,728 --> 00:11:07,052
Why do people around me keep on missing?

125
00:11:08,839 --> 00:11:10,279
So dramatic.

126
00:11:10,279 --> 00:11:10,954
Let’s leave.

127
00:11:10,954 --> 00:11:12,158
Let him play his music video.

128
00:11:31,234 --> 00:11:32,267
Ahem.

129
00:11:32,267 --> 00:11:33,234
Tun?

130
00:11:33,548 --> 00:11:35,548
We see you’re lonely so we’re keeping you company.

131
00:11:35,548 --> 00:11:37,033
We’ve got some beers.

132
00:11:37,033 --> 00:11:38,151
Come one.

133
00:11:42,001 --> 00:11:43,581
Let’s drink and watch a movie.

134
00:11:43,828 --> 00:11:44,960
It’s a long night tonight.

135
00:11:45,103 --> 00:11:46,515
Let’s watch the one you made.

136
00:11:46,826 --> 00:11:48,283
It just hit the streaming app.

137
00:11:50,075 --> 00:11:51,150
Sure.

138
00:12:00,558 --> 00:12:03,202
I designed the ending scene already.

139
00:12:03,272 --> 00:12:08,464
After the lead characters parted, they run into each other here one day.

140
00:12:10,342 --> 00:12:12,342
It’s my first snow in life.

141
00:12:13,339 --> 00:12:17,467
That means I’m the first one you see snow with.

142
00:12:21,572 --> 00:12:24,132
If this movie was aired in our universe,

143
00:12:24,467 --> 00:12:26,467
it would make millions by now.

144
00:12:27,128 --> 00:12:28,406
If it wasn’t for you,

145
00:12:29,128 --> 00:12:30,746
this movie wouldn’t have happened.

146
00:12:32,373 --> 00:12:33,401
I’m going to bed.

147
00:12:34,661 --> 00:12:35,633
Drowsy.

148
00:12:41,394 --> 00:12:42,358
Tun.

149
00:13:14,020 --> 00:13:15,684
I’m starving, Tess.

150
00:13:15,883 --> 00:13:17,127
Let’s go eat.

151
00:13:18,689 --> 00:13:19,588
Wake up.

152
00:13:22,276 --> 00:13:24,889
He’s never been a morning person.

153
00:13:26,002 --> 00:13:27,560
We must play hardball.

154
00:13:30,122 --> 00:13:30,968
Ready?

155
00:13:31,472 --> 00:13:34,306
1, 2, 3.

156
00:13:34,306 --> 00:13:36,248
Tickle. Tickle.

157
00:13:48,157 --> 00:13:49,338
Who are you here for?

158
00:13:49,338 --> 00:13:51,360
Is Tun home?

159
00:14:00,530 --> 00:14:02,838
He’s been like this since he got back.

160
00:14:02,838 --> 00:14:07,352
Spending alone time in his room, not associating with anyone.

161
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:09,862
It’s good you’re here, Tess. Please deal with him.

162
00:14:14,878 --> 00:14:15,898
Tun.

163
00:14:28,328 --> 00:14:29,151
Talay.

164
00:14:30,971 --> 00:14:32,148
What brought you here?

165
00:14:32,425 --> 00:14:36,413
It hasn’t even been that long but you look a lot older.

166
00:14:37,294 --> 00:14:38,650
Your ears are deaf.

167
00:14:40,052 --> 00:14:41,240
And look.

168
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:43,080
Your mustache has turned white.

169
00:14:49,567 --> 00:14:50,463
Yeah.

170
00:14:51,079 --> 00:14:52,680
Now you’re as old as me.

171
00:15:00,012 --> 00:15:01,256
What are you listening to?

172
00:15:02,831 --> 00:15:04,691
Some music.

173
00:15:04,935 --> 00:15:09,315
But I don’t know any of the songs in this universe.

174
00:15:10,804 --> 00:15:13,364
♪ Oh dear love ♪

175
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:16,412
♪ Please look at me ♪

176
00:15:16,783 --> 00:15:24,831
♪ Sometimes we meet on a heartbreaking day ♪

177
00:15:25,325 --> 00:15:33,065
♪ You come in and embrace me softly ♪

178
00:15:33,757 --> 00:15:36,233
♪ Oh dear love ♪

179
00:15:36,811 --> 00:15:39,035
♪ Sweet love ♪

180
00:15:39,499 --> 00:15:47,155
♪ You’re a beauty, my heart gets carried away ♪

181
00:15:47,701 --> 00:15:49,701
♪ Look at you ♪

182
00:15:50,568 --> 00:15:52,820
♪ Where are you? ♪

183
00:15:53,103 --> 00:15:58,239
♪ Oh dear love, I want to meet you ♪

184
00:15:59,848 --> 00:16:04,508
♪ You can do anything ♪

185
00:16:04,956 --> 00:16:12,192
♪ Oh dear love, I love you ♪

186
00:16:19,121 --> 00:16:20,729
The song you wanted to hear.

187
00:16:21,852 --> 00:16:23,120
I played it.

188
00:16:25,734 --> 00:16:26,978
I should leave now.

189
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:32,736
You came all the way here just to play me that song?

190
00:16:32,881 --> 00:16:34,881
You’ve been gone for 9 days.

191
00:16:35,616 --> 00:16:42,840
Do you have any idea how long 12,960 minutes I waited for you felt like?

192
00:16:45,781 --> 00:16:46,549
Tun.

193
00:16:47,832 --> 00:16:48,756
I…

194
00:16:51,751 --> 00:16:53,331
I freaking missed you.

195
00:16:56,946 --> 00:16:57,854
I know.

196
00:16:59,814 --> 00:17:01,270
Because for me,

197
00:17:01,739 --> 00:17:07,043
it was 777,600 seconds that I spent missing you like crazy too.

198
00:17:37,996 --> 00:17:38,909
What about you?

199
00:17:38,909 --> 00:17:40,416
What did you miss about me?

200
00:17:40,534 --> 00:17:41,638
I miss…

201
00:17:42,145 --> 00:17:43,720
your annoyance,

202
00:17:43,906 --> 00:17:45,486
your care,

203
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:47,200
and lastly,

204
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,218
just you.

205
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:50,687
Hey!

206
00:18:23,052 --> 00:18:24,309
I have a question.

207
00:18:25,169 --> 00:18:26,971
Why did you disappear?

208
00:18:28,305 --> 00:18:29,859
I don’t have much money left.

209
00:18:31,315 --> 00:18:33,712
And I don’t want to bother Pakorn’s parents.

210
00:18:35,009 --> 00:18:37,827
I tried to save money as much as I could.

211
00:18:39,221 --> 00:18:40,552
I stayed in.

212
00:18:41,407 --> 00:18:42,645
I didn’t contact anyone.

213
00:18:43,407 --> 00:18:44,367
I didn’t go anywhere.

214
00:18:45,651 --> 00:18:47,056
I only ate at home.

215
00:18:47,474 --> 00:18:48,879
Is it that bad?

216
00:18:51,039 --> 00:18:54,922
Then why didn’t you answer my calls?

217
00:18:56,265 --> 00:18:58,265
Because if you said you wanted to see me

218
00:18:59,131 --> 00:19:02,618
or if I heard your voice,

219
00:19:04,502 --> 00:19:07,939
I couldn’t resist going to see you, Talay.

220
00:19:15,003 --> 00:19:18,911
I tried to find a new job

221
00:19:19,437 --> 00:19:21,437
but there was no job I wanted to do.

222
00:19:22,384 --> 00:19:23,396
Why not?

223
00:19:25,007 --> 00:19:26,466
Because you were not part of it.

224
00:19:29,814 --> 00:19:35,556
A life of doing things alone was not fun at all.

225
00:19:39,579 --> 00:19:41,314
I think we…

226
00:19:41,314 --> 00:19:42,828
Tun, Tess,

227
00:19:42,828 --> 00:19:44,535
I prepared you guys some snacks.

228
00:19:44,535 --> 00:19:45,671
Come have some.

229
00:19:46,754 --> 00:19:47,837
Yes, Mom.

230
00:19:48,835 --> 00:19:49,929
Hello, Dad.

231
00:19:49,929 --> 00:19:50,835
Hello.

232
00:19:51,488 --> 00:19:53,488
Glad to finally meet you in person, Tess.

233
00:19:53,488 --> 00:19:56,920
Ever since Tun got home, he hasn’t talked about anything.

234
00:19:57,395 --> 00:19:58,618
He seems to forget everything.

235
00:19:58,816 --> 00:19:59,816
He only talked about one thing.

236
00:20:00,211 --> 00:20:00,913
You, Tess.

237
00:20:00,913 --> 00:20:02,211
Really, Dad?

238
00:20:02,642 --> 00:20:04,154
Did he gossip about me?

239
00:20:05,446 --> 00:20:06,314
No.

240
00:20:06,314 --> 00:20:08,603
He mainly said you’re great.

241
00:20:08,603 --> 00:20:10,609
You’re so helpful. Like when he was put in jail…

242
00:20:10,609 --> 00:20:11,654
Dad!

243
00:20:12,263 --> 00:20:13,474
That’s enough.

244
00:20:14,122 --> 00:20:16,494
Have you eaten anything yet, Tess?

245
00:20:16,494 --> 00:20:18,891
Can I make you anything? You guys can eat together.

246
00:20:19,227 --> 00:20:20,276
Thank you, Mom.

247
00:20:20,276 --> 00:20:21,354
I’m just hungry.

248
00:20:21,436 --> 00:20:23,932
Okay then. Just one second.

249
00:20:24,395 --> 00:20:26,395
Honey, come help me.

250
00:20:26,395 --> 00:20:27,672
Let the kids talk. Come here.

251
00:20:27,672 --> 00:20:28,629
Of course.

252
00:20:28,629 --> 00:20:29,493
Chop-chop.

253
00:20:32,198 --> 00:20:34,198
Pakorn’s parents are lovely.

254
00:20:34,198 --> 00:20:36,095
I guess this is such a warm family.

255
00:20:37,210 --> 00:20:38,434
So lovely.

256
00:20:38,661 --> 00:20:41,314
They always give Pakorn the things he likes.

257
00:20:42,229 --> 00:20:43,337
Here.

258
00:20:43,657 --> 00:20:45,037
Fill your stomach first.

259
00:20:49,306 --> 00:20:51,306
Pakorn must like this very much.

260
00:21:00,981 --> 00:21:02,981
I like it too.

261
00:21:08,010 --> 00:21:09,081
I mean you.

262
00:21:12,501 --> 00:21:13,653
What?

263
00:21:14,783 --> 00:21:16,783
I like when you eat.

264
00:21:17,189 --> 00:21:19,189
You make everything look so yummy.

265
00:21:22,517 --> 00:21:24,393
Then I’ll eat them all by myself.

266
00:21:33,589 --> 00:21:34,537
Who is it?

267
00:21:35,429 --> 00:21:36,828
I’ll go get the door.

268
00:21:37,634 --> 00:21:39,274
Don’t bother.

269
00:21:39,274 --> 00:21:40,670
I just invited myself in.

270
00:21:40,670 --> 00:21:41,845
I came very often.

271
00:21:42,394 --> 00:21:43,389
How have you been?

272
00:21:43,389 --> 00:21:44,320
I missed you guys.

273
00:21:44,739 --> 00:21:46,314
I brought you guys northern Thai sausages.

274
00:21:46,856 --> 00:21:47,921
Up!

275
00:21:47,921 --> 00:21:49,153
What brings you here?

276
00:21:49,582 --> 00:21:51,582
I missed your foul mouth so bad.

277
00:21:51,582 --> 00:21:52,401
I know.

278
00:21:52,401 --> 00:21:53,645
I’m so proud of it.

279
00:21:53,937 --> 00:21:56,474
Now that we’re here, should we call Aou?

280
00:21:56,474 --> 00:21:57,002
Do it.

281
00:21:57,002 --> 00:21:57,948
Go ahead, Tess.

282
00:22:03,695 --> 00:22:05,150
Hi, Aou.

283
00:22:05,798 --> 00:22:06,958
(Hello. Hello.)

284
00:22:07,874 --> 00:22:09,284
(What did you say?)

285
00:22:09,284 --> 00:22:10,964
(I have no reception.)

286
00:22:12,061 --> 00:22:13,466
(Hello. Hello.)

287
00:22:14,170 --> 00:22:15,848
He’s probably doing some fishing.

288
00:22:15,848 --> 00:22:16,951
He said he had no reception.

289
00:22:16,951 --> 00:22:19,273
Uh…okay.

290
00:22:19,273 --> 00:22:20,584
I just got my reception.

291
00:22:20,584 --> 00:22:22,477
It’s nice and clear now.

292
00:22:23,045 --> 00:22:24,450
Aou!

293
00:22:24,450 --> 00:22:25,851
You. You. You.

294
00:22:28,684 --> 00:22:29,965
Like that?

295
00:22:30,641 --> 00:22:32,914
Hold on. I’m lost.

296
00:22:33,853 --> 00:22:35,234
Is this destiny?

297
00:22:35,353 --> 00:22:37,353
There’s no such a thing.

298
00:22:37,353 --> 00:22:39,176
I destined this.

299
00:22:39,511 --> 00:22:42,800
After you came, I called them here too.

300
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:44,952
Luckily, they are in Bangkok.

301
00:22:45,102 --> 00:22:46,879
I freaking missed you guys.

302
00:22:48,419 --> 00:22:49,154
Guys.

303
00:22:50,715 --> 00:22:53,616
Friend Credits!

304
00:22:56,242 --> 00:22:58,713
