305
00:22:59,277 --> 00:23:00,251
But first,

306
00:23:01,416 --> 00:23:03,034
I need something to eat.

307
00:23:03,158 --> 00:23:04,026
Stop.

308
00:23:04,525 --> 00:23:05,806
You can’t eat these.

309
00:23:08,868 --> 00:23:10,967
They’ve been reserved.

310
00:23:11,186 --> 00:23:12,963
He said he would eat them all by himself.

311
00:23:25,803 --> 00:23:27,208
No way.

312
00:23:27,382 --> 00:23:28,911
Stop!

313
00:23:29,409 --> 00:23:31,045
Nobody can have it.

314
00:23:32,476 --> 00:23:33,386
Fine.

315
00:23:38,037 --> 00:23:40,830
Friend Credits!

316
00:23:46,664 --> 00:23:47,483
What?

317
00:23:47,979 --> 00:23:49,434
It sparkled for a few seconds.

318
00:23:51,928 --> 00:23:52,972
The sparkler?

319
00:23:53,493 --> 00:23:54,449
You want more?

320
00:23:55,237 --> 00:23:56,766
I meant us.

321
00:23:57,382 --> 00:23:59,209
We shone for a short moment.

322
00:24:01,315 --> 00:24:02,547
But I think…

323
00:24:03,063 --> 00:24:04,674
we can go further.

324
00:24:04,811 --> 00:24:06,514
That was just one failure.

325
00:24:06,646 --> 00:24:08,051
Should we make more movies?

326
00:24:08,487 --> 00:24:10,165
Make more failures.

327
00:24:10,165 --> 00:24:10,882
No.

328
00:24:14,645 --> 00:24:15,827
How sad.

329
00:24:16,790 --> 00:24:19,234
Because it won’t be a failure this time.

330
00:24:26,968 --> 00:24:28,844
Yes!

331
00:24:35,914 --> 00:24:36,961
What about you, Tess?

332
00:24:37,655 --> 00:24:39,714
Would you like to work with us one more time?

333
00:24:40,429 --> 00:24:41,219
Let’s do it.

334
00:24:41,616 --> 00:24:42,826
Go as far as we can.

335
00:24:43,159 --> 00:24:44,787
I’ll talk to my dad.

336
00:24:45,038 --> 00:24:46,840
To our brighter day.

337
00:24:47,382 --> 00:24:49,382
Cheers.

338
00:24:49,382 --> 00:24:52,554
Cheers!

339
00:24:57,996 --> 00:25:01,136
You know, I missed you guys so bad.

340
00:25:01,274 --> 00:25:03,274
I missed everything about you.

341
00:25:03,274 --> 00:25:05,317
Every personality you guys have.

342
00:25:05,354 --> 00:25:06,203
Like what?

343
00:25:06,636 --> 00:25:08,066
You, for example, Up.

344
00:25:08,066 --> 00:25:10,354
I missed your friendliness so much.

345
00:25:10,699 --> 00:25:14,236
You make people smile while they don’t even have to ask for it.

346
00:25:14,236 --> 00:25:18,501
And I missed your annoying aggressiveness and inappropriate behaviors.

347
00:25:18,501 --> 00:25:19,640
You’re picking on me, clearly.

348
00:25:20,369 --> 00:25:23,038
Hey, but I truly missed you all.

349
00:25:32,768 --> 00:25:33,508
What about you?

350
00:25:33,979 --> 00:25:35,561
What did you miss about me?

351
00:25:38,244 --> 00:25:39,247
That’s tough.

352
00:25:39,941 --> 00:25:40,938
Can’t think of one.

353
00:25:42,411 --> 00:25:43,674
Nothing at all?

354
00:25:58,189 --> 00:26:00,189
I missed…

355
00:26:02,209 --> 00:26:03,713
your annoyance,

356
00:26:05,499 --> 00:26:07,003
your shyness,

357
00:26:08,027 --> 00:26:09,581
your nice singing voice,

358
00:26:13,161 --> 00:26:14,566
your care,

359
00:26:16,834 --> 00:26:18,289
and lastly,

360
00:26:21,348 --> 00:26:22,380
just you.

361
00:26:26,594 --> 00:26:27,339
Hey!

362
00:26:28,938 --> 00:26:30,634
You’re not sleeping?

363
00:26:35,055 --> 00:26:36,584
I was.

364
00:26:37,448 --> 00:26:39,944
But then I heard your whispering sound.

365
00:26:40,367 --> 00:26:41,673
It woke me up.

366
00:26:44,035 --> 00:26:45,614
Were you talking behind my back?

367
00:26:46,075 --> 00:26:47,530
No.

368
00:26:50,107 --> 00:26:51,123
Nothing.

369
00:26:51,569 --> 00:26:52,553
Just sleep.

370
00:26:54,933 --> 00:26:56,314
I can’t anymore.

371
00:26:56,776 --> 00:26:57,886
Take responsibility.

372
00:26:58,307 --> 00:26:59,494
Make me drowsy.

373
00:27:02,102 --> 00:27:03,681
How about counting sheep?

374
00:27:04,514 --> 00:27:05,919
I don’t have any other ideas.

375
00:27:14,070 --> 00:27:15,872
I read this from a book.

376
00:27:16,253 --> 00:27:20,335
It says if we hear the sound of nature before going to bed,

377
00:27:20,934 --> 00:27:22,661
we will fall asleep easier.

378
00:27:24,055 --> 00:27:25,187
The sound of nature?

379
00:27:25,881 --> 00:27:26,749
What is it?

380
00:27:31,450 --> 00:27:32,432
Talay. (The sea)

381
00:27:32,829 --> 00:27:34,144
I like the sound of the sea.

382
00:27:38,328 --> 00:27:40,328
Whisper in my ear now.

383
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:02,597
What the heck are you doing?

384
00:28:03,613 --> 00:28:04,593
Making the wave sound.

385
00:28:07,099 --> 00:28:08,674
My ears are all wet.

386
00:28:15,337 --> 00:28:17,213
Should we try patting your back and your butt?

387
00:28:18,237 --> 00:28:20,014
I did it when I nannied my nephew.

388
00:28:22,254 --> 00:28:23,401
I was about to say that.

389
00:28:24,254 --> 00:28:25,914
How old are you?

390
00:28:27,954 --> 00:28:33,597
I think you should just stop talking and you’ll be drowsy soon.

391
00:28:43,110 --> 00:28:44,515
That’s a big yawn.

392
00:28:46,210 --> 00:28:48,383
And now you’re the one drowsy.

393
00:28:56,436 --> 00:28:57,331
Hey.

394
00:28:57,331 --> 00:28:58,857
There’s one last method.

395
00:28:58,955 --> 00:28:59,997
Ear massage.

396
00:29:00,641 --> 00:29:02,541
I’ll do it for you.

397
00:29:03,380 --> 00:29:04,413
Um.

398
00:29:33,699 --> 00:29:34,884
Good night,

399
00:29:35,798 --> 00:29:36,613
Talay.

400
00:29:51,514 --> 00:29:53,834
Signs you’re falling in love.

401
00:29:55,195 --> 00:29:56,600
There!

402
00:29:57,064 --> 00:29:58,066
I saw that.

403
00:29:58,066 --> 00:29:59,434
Who are you falling in love with?

404
00:30:00,786 --> 00:30:01,526
Speak.

405
00:30:02,786 --> 00:30:04,046
You’re wrong.

406
00:30:04,192 --> 00:30:06,712
I’m just doing some research for my romantic movie.

407
00:30:06,712 --> 00:30:08,596
Is that so?

408
00:30:09,517 --> 00:30:11,114
Let me know if you need a protagonist.

409
00:30:11,213 --> 00:30:12,705
I’m always up for it.

410
00:30:17,717 --> 00:30:19,717
Now that we talk about it.

411
00:30:20,623 --> 00:30:28,769
I want to know how we can tell if we like that person already.

412
00:30:31,544 --> 00:30:33,544
You’ve dated so many people.

413
00:30:33,774 --> 00:30:36,314
Why being so naive now?

414
00:30:38,051 --> 00:30:44,611
I just feel like I don’t know love at all.

415
00:30:45,544 --> 00:30:47,316
Sounds like a super dreamy dialogue from a movie.

416
00:30:47,937 --> 00:30:51,994
To me, to want that person in life is considered liking.

417
00:30:52,880 --> 00:30:53,811
That’s it?

418
00:30:53,811 --> 00:30:54,880
Heck yeah.

419
00:30:55,398 --> 00:30:56,429
Don’t overthink it.

420
00:30:56,726 --> 00:30:58,394
Don’t complicate things.

421
00:31:01,714 --> 00:31:02,975
So…

422
00:31:03,223 --> 00:31:06,490
Who are you feeling it with?

423
00:31:07,914 --> 00:31:09,474
I told you, no one.

424
00:31:09,737 --> 00:31:11,737
You think I don’t know.

425
00:31:11,737 --> 00:31:12,617
- You…
- Shut it.

426
00:31:13,137 --> 00:31:13,916
Stop talking.

427
00:31:19,941 --> 00:31:21,083
What are you afraid of, Tess?

428
00:31:21,314 --> 00:31:26,194
You don’t need to be afraid of failing in the end.

429
00:31:29,162 --> 00:31:30,468
What you should be afraid of

430
00:31:31,802 --> 00:31:33,802
is letting that person slip through your fingers.

431
00:31:39,946 --> 00:31:40,836
Whose RV is that?

432
00:31:41,274 --> 00:31:42,754
It belonged to a friend of my dad.

433
00:31:42,754 --> 00:31:44,545
How about we renovate it into a studio?

434
00:31:44,545 --> 00:31:45,918
It’s an RV.

435
00:31:46,204 --> 00:31:48,204
I’ve always wanted to have an RV.

436
00:31:48,204 --> 00:31:49,304
Just like in this photo.

437
00:31:49,304 --> 00:31:51,287
But I think it is missing something.

438
00:31:51,287 --> 00:31:52,092
What?

439
00:31:52,092 --> 00:31:55,535
Someone who’s willing to travel with you for the rest of your life.

440
00:32:34,372 --> 00:32:35,707
What you should be afraid of

441
00:32:37,661 --> 00:32:39,504
is letting that person slip through your fingers.

442
00:32:48,220 --> 00:32:50,360
What the hell are you playing, Tun?

443
00:32:51,075 --> 00:32:53,075
Are you playing a sad guy in a music video?

444
00:32:53,968 --> 00:32:54,837
No.

445
00:32:55,799 --> 00:32:57,787
I’m just thinking

446
00:32:58,517 --> 00:33:00,045
about our next movie project.

447
00:33:00,515 --> 00:33:01,612
What are you doing here?

448
00:33:02,801 --> 00:33:04,858
I was helping my dad water the plants.

449
00:33:04,964 --> 00:33:06,544
Then I saw you making an awkward face.

450
00:33:06,663 --> 00:33:07,627
So I decided to watch you instead.

451
00:33:07,627 --> 00:33:08,392
Pleasing to the eye.

452
00:33:09,243 --> 00:33:10,561
Get lost.

453
00:33:13,572 --> 00:33:14,905
I said go.

454
00:33:21,762 --> 00:33:22,429
Tun.

455
00:33:22,792 --> 00:33:23,383
Hm?

456
00:33:23,567 --> 00:33:24,487
Whose RV is that?

457
00:33:26,359 --> 00:33:27,387
That one?

458
00:33:29,552 --> 00:33:30,952
It belonged to a friend of my dad.

459
00:33:31,322 --> 00:33:33,759
My dad told me his friend needed money.

460
00:33:33,876 --> 00:33:35,439
He sold it to my dad for a good price.

461
00:33:35,439 --> 00:33:38,524
Your dad bought it and left it like this?

462
00:33:39,832 --> 00:33:41,412
He doesn’t know how to make use of it.

463
00:33:41,412 --> 00:33:42,760
It goes at the speed of a turtle.

